title: ULTRASOUND LEFT UPPER EXTEMITY VEINS

technique.description: Ultrasound images of the left upper extremity veins acquired. Color and spectral Doppler images also acquired.

findings.deep: No thrombus in the left internal jugular, subclavian, axillary, and brachial veins.
findings.superficial: Left basilic and cephalic veins are compressible.

impression: No deep venous thrombis in the left upper extremity.
